[The Upper Peninsula (UP) is the northern of the 2 major peninsulas that make up the US state of Michigan; the UP is bounded on the north by Lake Superior, on the east by Ontario, Canada, on the south by Lake Michigan and Lake Huron, and on the west by northeastern Wisconsin; the Mackinac Bridge connects the Lower Peninsula of Michigan with the UP (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upper_Peninsula_of_Michigan). There are 15 counties in the UP, which include Dickinson, Iron, Delta, Menominee and Marquette. A map of Michigan counties can be found at https://geology.com/county-map/michigan.shtml. - Mod.ML]

